Project README

Last rendered: 2017-01-26 12:17:31


This README documents the scripts contained in the github repo and demonstrates their use to conduct analyses relating to the bird trait networks project.

Description is split into project set up and the various analyses attempted during the project.

Project setup


get access to code:

The ideal method to access the code is the through checking it out from the master github folder. It is worth spending on time to set this up properly so heres more on github through Rstudio, setting yourself up on github and Rstudio and forking & linking projects through RStudio

You can create a static local implementation of the project by just downloading the github repo as a ZIP:

unzipping it and supplying the path to the unzipped folder to parameter script.folder. You will not be able to automatically update code with changes to the master repo however so not recommended.


configure project - edit file_setup.R

To initiate a project locally, the first thing to do is edit script file_setup.R to specify the paths to:

1. Folder containing the data (the googledrive folder)

The best way to access the data is through authorised access through googledrive. Youll need to install googledrive on your system to enable this.

Once installed, youll be able to programmatically access files (see example below), by specifying your local path to the folder. Analyses will also always be synched to most up to date version of data.

output.folder <- "/Users/Anna/Google Drive/bird trait networks/outputs/"
input.folder <- "/Users/Anna/Google Drive/bird trait networks/inputs/data/"
data.folder <- "/Users/Anna/Google Drive/bird trait networks/"


2. Folder containing the code (the github folder)

Ideally it is the path to an Rstudio project, checked out from the master github folder

script.folder <- "~/Documents/workflows/bird_trait_networks/"


set up file.system

set path to file_setup.R script and source

file_setup_path <- "~/Documents/workflows/bird_trait_networks/file_setup.R"
source(file_setup_path)


initialise an analysis environment.


specify environment

Specify environment through setting "param" or "wkf".

  • param should a character string of the name of a script in params/ folder. Use this folder to store parametarisations of the environment to be called.
  • "wkf" specifies the workflow you wish to load in the environment

e.g.

wkf = "phylonetworker"
param = "phylonetworker.R"

if no "param" or "wkf" is specified, sourcing project_ui.R initalises a base global envrionment.

source project_ui.R

source(paste(script.folder, "project_ui.R", sep = ""))

see project_ui README for more

Workflows ("wkf") within the project

  • rmacroRDM:

    Addition of the amniote database to originally supplied data. Outputs, long and aggregated wide versions of the data. Current analysis in "master workflow.R"

  • phylonetworker:

    network analysis of phylogenetically corrected correlation between traits, current analysis in "PhyloNeworker.R"

  • mgm:

    network analysis of mgm derived associations of trait marginal relationship, performed on imputed data. Current analysis in "mgm.R". Use reports/results/mgm_viz.Rmd to visualise anaysis

  • goodmankruskal:

    goodmanKruskal determination (GKtau) on categorical variables and network analysis of outputs. current analysis in "goodmankruskal.R"

Other useful documents


Public

  • data_gap_eval:

    Evaluation of data avalaibility in response to min.n and resulting biases.

  • Network_Data_Availability:

    Evaluation of trait pair data avalaibility (full data). Network_Data_Availability.Rmd generating script in man/ folder in repo.

  • Network_Data_Availability_100spp:

    Evaluation of trait pair data avalaibility (100spp data). Network_Data_Availability 100spp.Rmd generating script in man/ folder in repo.

  • Hierarchical Networks:

    Report on Hierarchical network theory and tools. Hierarchical Networks.Rmd generating script in man/ folder in repo.


Sensitive (in outputs/Reports/Results folder on Googledrive)

  • Categorical_phylocors.html

    examination of phylogenetically simulated vs observed GoodmanKruskal of categorical variables. Categorical_phylocors.Rmd generating script in reports/results/ folder in repo.

  • Network_viz.html

    results of phylonetworker analysis. Network_viz.Rmd generating script in reports/results/ folder in repo.

  • CorNetwork plots.html

    early network visualisation report. CorNetwork plots.Rmd generating script in reports/results/ folder in repo.
